The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 02 February is 202,406 (23,328.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 28 January, there were 11,180 new confirmed cases (1,288.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 21 January, there were 9,877 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 13% (1,303 extra cases).
